query:
-- Get San Joaquin County ID first
SET @sjc_id = (SELECT id FROM counties WHERE name LIKE '%San Joaquin%' AND state = 'California' LIMIT 1);

-- Insert Adult Cardiac protocols
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, protocolEffectiveDate, protocolYear, createdAt)
VALUES 
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-01', 'Cardiac Arrest', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Cardiac Arrest. Includes CPR, defibrillation, airway management, IV/IO access, and medication administration per ACLS guidelines.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-02', 'Asystole/PEA', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Asystole and Pulseless Electrical Activity. Focus on high-quality CPR, epinephrine administration, and identifying reversible causes (Hs and Ts).', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-03', 'V-Fib/Pulseless V-Tach', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Ventricular Fibrillation and Pulseless Ventricular Tachycardia. Includes defibrillation, CPR, epinephrine, and amiodarone.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-04', 'Post Resuscitation (ROSC)', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Return of Spontaneous Circulation. Post-cardiac arrest care including airway management, hemodynamic support, and targeted temperature management consideration.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-05', 'Bradycardia', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Bradycardia. Assessment of hemodynamic stability, atropine administration, transcutaneous pacing, and dopamine/epinephrine infusion.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-06', 'Tachycardia', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Tachycardia. Differentiation between stable and unstable, narrow vs wide complex, vagal maneuvers, adenosine, and synchronized cardioversion.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-07', 'Chest Pain/ACS', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Chest Pain and Acute Coronary Syndrome. 12-lead ECG, aspirin, nitroglycerin, morphine, and STEMI activation criteria.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ACAR-08', 'Cardiogenic Shock', 'Adult Cardiac', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Cardiogenic Shock. Fluid resuscitation, vasopressor support, and transport to appropriate facility.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW());
